The paper proposes algorithms for optimization problems, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. Specifically, the paper focuses on stochastic optimization and variance reduction techniques, which are widely used in large-scale machine learning problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses optimization techniques for nonconvex problems, which are relevant to the optimization community, making cs.OC (Optimization and Control) a likely category as well. Finally, the paper explores the acceleration brought by third-order smoothness of the objective function, which is a topic of interest in numerical analysis, making cs.NE (Numerical Analysis) a possible category.
